    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-12T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-12T13:00:00-05:00" n="405"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/2574: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Seville</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seville</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-12T18:00:00+00:00"
                            >August 12, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 13—1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. Merida was taken by military forces yesterday afternoon thus effecting
                    junction with General Mola’s forces which hold Caceres. Fall of Merida also
                    opens two principal highways to Madrid from the south.</p>
                <p>Following war material arrived in Seville August 9:10 new Savoia tri-motor
                    bombing aeroplanes with about 20 Italian pilots, 18 Junker <pb facs="0581"
                        n="482" xml:id="pg_482"/> tri-motor bombers mostly new with about 30 German
                    pilots, 2 additional units of similar kind to arrive later, 6 German pursuit
                    planes capable of 450 kilometers and 6 German anti-aircraft guns of latest model
                    with effective range of 700 meters. Ships are being tuned up and Spanish
                    aviators are being instructed in their operation. First objectives are said to
                    be: elimination Madrid aircraft which are preventing army of General Mola from
                    deploying into plains before Madrid, destruction of Madrid airfield and Spanish
                    warships in Straits of Gibraltar.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
